labels.value: I initially started my undergraduate education at Franklin College in Fall of 2012 as a Computer Science major. Franklin College is located in Indiana, and Franklin itself is the small town just South of Indianapolis I grew up in. However, after two years I transferred to the University of South Florida Sarasota-Manatee in Fall of 2015 in order to be closer to my parents that had moved to the area themselves a year prior. Unfortunately, they did not have a Computer Science major. However, the program still offered me the education and tools needed to pursue a career path in the general IT field.

The only downside is I wanted to pursue a career path in development or engineering. Having graduated in Spring of 2018, I spent the majority of that summer looking for a job, and when I wasn't doing that I was learning, coding, and filling in the missing gaps so I could land a job as a developer. Luckily when it rains it pours, and during a one week span in August of 2018 I was offered three jobs. One as a PHP developer, the second as an intern to full-time C#/.NET developer, and the final one being the Application Support Analyst with J&J. I ended taking up the position with J&J as I could not pass up on the chance to work with such a great company and work my way towards a developer role.
BS, Information Technology, Applications and Web Development Concentration
